e=1> This is an item that is attainable and i really think we should look at doing this a few times if possible<br>
 <br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP  <br>
Damage: 10<br>
Delay: 18 <br>
Ratio: 1.8 Amazing <br>
Str: +5 Sta: +5 Wis: +8 HP: +35  <br>
Weight: 3.0 <br>
Weapon Skill: One Hand Slash <br>
Classes: Ranger Paladin Shadowknight Bard Warrior  <br>
Races: All Races  <br>
Inventory Slot: Either Melee<br>
SOL Required: Yes <br>
<br>
<br>
*General Jared Blaystich, 55th warrior. <br>
*Echo Caverns, in the secret bandit area with the caster trainers in the castle on the right. Upstairs with 2 guards. <br>
*1 damage dealer, 2 clerics could do him. Would suggest a 2nd tank for the pull. Rogue, monk, cleric, cleric works good. <br>
*Sit straight out from the castle, against the wall, stay away from the cleric trainer on the right hilltop. <br>
*Single pull the two outside guards. <br>
*Have one person stand next to the general (invis if kos) and one person outside. <br>
*The person outside, casts, throws, whatever on the left trainer inside (A gnome with a oracle robe look). <br>
*Haul ass fast for the zone. The 4 trainers hit up to 400 and cast 50th spells. <br>
*Person waits at the zone til they see all 4 caster trainers come into view and then zones after telling the group to pull. <br>
*The person next to the general nails him and runs out of the castle to the group at the wall. <br>
*Make sure you fight the general at the wall so the returning caster trainers dont jump you. They will spend about 5 seconds killing the guards at the zoneline before returning. <br>
*Slow and movement altering spells dont land, dont bother. He doesnt rampage so dont bother with cripple. <br>
*Kill the 2 guards that come with the general first, they are easier than frogloks in lguk. <br>
*As said before, mok and mor land. The general hits for under 200 damage, double shots, and semi fast. Will need a cleric or two depending on mana regen and tank hp. CH at 2 bars and there will be no problems. Cant remember if he enrages or not. He has alot of hit points. <br>
*Dispel him a few times, the various trainers in the area with him buff him (haste, etc). <br>
*The general doesnt run, drops the sword, and a no rent shield. All the others drop a note, I assume is for some quest. <br>
*24 hour +/- 1 hour spawn time.  <p>Imas Illusion                        
